  "text": "Triglycine sulfate (TGS) is the archetypal organic hydrogen-bonded molecular ferroelectric: two glycinium cations, one neutral glycine, and one sulfate anion linked by N\u2013H\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7O and O\u2013H\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7O hydrogen bonds. Below its Curie point (\u224847.5 \u00b0C \u2248 321 K) it adopts the polar monoclinic space group P2\u2081 (point group 2) and is ferroelectric, pyroelectric, and piezoelectric; above Tc it transforms to the centrosymmetric paraelectric P2\u2081/m phase (point group 2/m), which is non-piezoelectric. The room-temperature (298 K) ferroelectric structure here was determined by time-of-flight neutron diffraction (Terasawa et al., 2022); the piezoelectric constants were measured by Ikeda, Tanaka & Toyoda (1962).",

